add

public MitigationExpiration add(MitigationExpiration exp)
Add the given MitigationExpiration to this Identity. This will remove an existing mitigation before adding the new mitigation if there is already a mitigation expiration for this same entitlement requested from the same type of certification. This allows, for example, a manager to mitigate a business role in one certification report and later re-mitigate it to extend the mitigation period. The caller should delete the returned MitigationExpiration if one is returned.

Parameters:
exp - The MitigationExpiration to add to this identity.
Returns:
A removed MitigationExpiration if adding this expiration obsoleted an older expiration. The caller should delete this.
